As a matter of fact,
we've been talking

00:25:43.350 --> 00:25:45.791
with Shane Smith and Vice.

00:25:45.791 --> 00:25:47.791
We've been talking with
a few other broadcasters

00:25:47.791 --> 00:25:51.560
about ramping up our
content and production.

00:25:51.560 --> 00:25:54.714
We want to be broadcasting
24/7 around the world.

00:25:54.714 --> 00:25:57.130
MARC DE SCHWEINITZ: And there's
so much content on YouTube

00:25:57.130 --> 00:25:57.860
right now.

00:25:57.860 --> 00:25:59.943
How do you cut through
that clutter and stand out?

00:25:59.943 --> 00:26:02.780
I've seen some of your videos
have hundreds of thousands

00:26:02.780 --> 00:26:04.990
of views, and
organically, I believe?

00:26:04.990 --> 00:26:07.540
TOM MCPHEE: Yeah, well,
it's building relationships.

